stories.text:
A friend and I have been working on a tag-based knowledge management thing to help you organize, well, anything - docs, photos, YouTube videos, Notion pages, whatever.

We're now working on a super cool auto-tagging, similar idea to Google Photos but with 2 unique things:

1. You can manually change any tag, delete, add, merge tags, etc.. 2. We tag photos but also docs, PDFs, and we might be adding more if there's interest.

Be brutal - would you use this?

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-OWUP9OvyCg

Or sign up to get notified when it's ready here: https://www.tagbox.io/knowledge-management-auto-tagging
